text: Kashubian Americans are Americans of Kashubian descent.see Fr. Władysław Szulist, Kaszubi w Ameryce: szkice i materiały, Wejherowo 2005. The two earliest Kashubian American settlements in the United States were located around Winona, Minnesota, and Portage County, Wisconsin, which are across the Mississippi River from each other. ==References== Category:Ethnic groups in the United States Americans
title: Kashubian Americans
